<title>USA: Xionics, Xerographic scrap merger.</title>
<headline>Xionics, Xerographic scrap merger.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-12-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Xionics Document Technologies Inc and Xerographic Laser Images Corp said they scrapped their plan for Xionics to buy Xerographic for about $5.2 million in stock and cash.</p>
<p>Both Xionics and Xerographic came to the decision amicably, the companies said, adding that their interests would be best served by Xerographic remaining an independent technology developer.</p>
<p>The companies added that they expect to maintain a strong relationship and are now working together, as announced, on Xerographic's resolution enhancement technology, which Xionics has licensed to integrate into its processors.</p>
</text>
